What are the houses like in my neighbourhood?

An exploration of house characteristics in my neighbourhood based on in-person observations, recorded manually and logged into a Google spreadsheet

What architectural style are they?

I counted 54 houses in total

In project 2, I looked at all the houses on my street, Rahiri Rd. For project 4, I looked at all the houses on a neighbouring street, Cedar Rd

Most houses in Mount Eden were built between the 1910s and 1930s, where common styles that emerged include bungalows and Victorian villas

Colours and sizes?

I appears that there are some pretty sizable differences in average floor area between house colour. Given the small sample size, I believe that these findings will not be the same for a larger sample of houses in the area

Do more bedrooms lead to a bigger house?

From the plot, we see a clear trend where floor area increases with number of bedrooms. It appears that the style of house doesnt really have a pattern with these variables

In Annas example, I really liked how each plot logically flowed from the one before it, creating a cohesive narrative. I tried my very best to achieve that in my work.
However, I also feel like we are disadvantaged because we have a much smaller sample size and did not collect data over many years.
